File: Several media reports suggested that the SANDF would be deployed from Wednesday. JOHANNESBURG - The SANDF says it cannot confirm or deny reports that the army will be deployed to help curb the coronavirus outbreak in the country. It says President Cyril Ramaphosa will comment on the matter. This comes after media reports suggested that the army would be deployed from Wednesday. READ: Confirmed COVID-19 cases increase by 34 One Sunday newspaper reported that leave for all SANDF members has been cancelled. It further added that soldiers have been told to prepare for short-term deployment. Several measures like travel bans and prohibition of meetings of over a hundred people have been implemented. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.